## Testing Pyramid

```
         /‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\
        /  E2E (Playwright)     \  ← Critical user journeys only
       /‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\
      /  Integration (Vitest)    \ ← Feature slices — real components + MSW
     /‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\
    /  Component (Vitest + RTL)   \ ← UI behavior, interactions, render states
   /‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\
  /  Unit (Vitest)                 \ ← Pure functions, hooks, utilities
 /‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\
```

Write the lowest-level test that gives you confidence. Move up a layer only when the layer below cannot adequately test the behavior.

