## Test Naming and Structure

### Name the behavior, not the code path

Test names are read when tests fail. Write them so a failing test tells you exactly what the user can no longer do.

```typescript
// ✅ Describes observable behavior
it('shows a critical badge when alert severity is critical')
it('calls onDismiss with the alert ID when the dismiss button is clicked')
it('displays an error message when the alerts request fails')

// ❌ Describes implementation — meaningless when it fails
it('renders correctly')
it('handleDismiss works')
it('returns the right value')
```

### AAA: Arrange, Act, Assert

Single-step tests have three sections. Multi-step interaction tests may have sequential Act-Assert pairs, but Arrange is always first and never repeated.

```typescript
// Single-step — three clean sections
it('filters resolved alerts from the active count', () => {
  // Arrange
  const alerts = [makeAlert({ status: 'active' }), makeAlert({ status: 'resolved' })];

  // Act
  const result = getActiveAlerts(alerts);

  // Assert
  expect(result).toHaveLength(1);
  expect(result[0].status).toBe('active');
});

// Multi-step interaction — Act-Assert repeats, Arrange stays at the top
it('updates the count after an alert is dismissed', async () => {
  // Arrange
  const user = userEvent.setup();
  render(<AlertsFeature />);
  await screen.findByText('3 active alerts'); // wait for initial load

  // Act → Assert (step 1)
  await user.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /dismiss exposed api key/i }));
  await screen.findByText('2 active alerts');

  // Act → Assert (step 2)
  await user.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /dismiss weak cipher/i }));
  await screen.findByText('1 active alert');
});
```

### `describe` blocks: group by behavior cluster, not by file

```typescript
// ✅
describe('AlertCard', () => {
  describe('severity badge', () => {
    it('shows "Critical" for critical severity')
    it('shows "Low" for low severity')
  });
  describe('dismiss action', () => {
    it('renders no dismiss button when onDismiss is not provided')
    it('calls onDismiss with the alert ID when clicked')
  });
});
```

