## Timer Mocking (Vitest)

Use `vi.useFakeTimers()` for polling intervals, debounce, and auto-dismiss behavior. Restore real timers in `afterEach`.

```typescript
describe('useAlertPoller', () => {
  beforeEach(() => vi.useFakeTimers());
  afterEach(() => vi.useRealTimers());

  it('re-fetches alerts every 30 seconds', async () => {
    const fetchSpy = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue([makeAlert()]);
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useAlertPoller(), { wrapper: createWrapper() });

    await waitFor(() => expect(fetchSpy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1));

    vi.advanceTimersByTime(30_000);
    await waitFor(() => expect(fetchSpy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2));
  });
});
```

