## Coverage Philosophy

Coverage is a floor, not a goal. 100% coverage with tests that verify the wrong thing is worthless.

**Target thresholds (enforce in CI):**

| Layer | Target | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Utilities / pure functions | 90%+ | Cheap to test exhaustively |
| Hooks | 80%+ | Core logic — errors are expensive |
| Components | 70%+ | Happy path + key states |
| Integration | No threshold | Quality over quantity |
| E2E | No threshold | Critical paths only |

**What coverage cannot tell you:**
- Whether your tests assert the right thing
- Whether error states are handled correctly
- Whether the UI is accessible

---

## What Not to Test

| Skip | Why |
|---|---|
| Third-party library internals | React, React Query, Zustand are tested by their maintainers |
| CSS classes and visual appearance | Verify with Storybook + visual diff tooling |
| Snapshot tests for UI components | Approve silently, break on every render — false confidence |
| Props passed through to child components | Structural, not behavioral — test what the user sees |
| TypeScript types at runtime | The compiler enforces types; runtime type assertions are redundant |
| Trivial pass-through wrappers | A component that renders `<div>{children}</div>` needs no test |

```typescript
// ❌ Snapshot — passes silently on any change
expect(render(<AlertCard {...makeAlert()} />).container).toMatchSnapshot();

// ❌ Prop-passing assertion — implementation detail
expect(AlertBadge).toHaveBeenCalledWith({ severity: 'critical' }, {});

// ✅
expect(screen.getByText('Critical')).toBeInTheDocument();
```

---

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-pattern | Risk | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `getByTestId` as default query | Survives invisible refactors, breaks semantic contract | `getByRole` first |
| `fireEvent` instead of `userEvent` | Misses focus, blur, validation chain | `userEvent.setup()` always |
| `new Promise(() => {})` for loading state | Leaks across tests, causes Vitest warnings | `HttpResponse.json(data, { delay: Infinity })` |
| `waitFor` wrapping multiple assertions | First passing assertion short-circuits the rest | One assertion per `waitFor` |
| `page.waitForTimeout` in Playwright | Slow and still flaky | Playwright auto-retrying assertions |
| `vi.mock` for API calls | Breaks on file rename | MSW handler |
| Snapshot tests | False confidence, noisy diffs | Explicit behavioral assertions |
| `afterEach(() => server.resetHandlers())` missing | Handler overrides bleed into adjacent tests | Enforced in `setupTests.ts` |
| `toHaveBeenCalled` without `toHaveBeenCalledWith` | Confirms invocation, not correctness | Always assert the arguments |
| Static fixtures for complex objects | Break all at once on type change | Typed factory with defaults |
| Skipping a flaky test | Erodes trust in the suite | Fix the root cause or delete the test |
